DOWNLOADER.GA -> Installation
------------^0o0^------------

0. Download files.

1. Mount ISO:

sudo mount [Downloader.ga]R2018a_glnxa64_dvd1.iso /mnt/cdrom -o loop
(
	if not folder 'cdrom' in 'mnt' then need to creat it first:
		sudo mkdir -p /mnt/cdrom
)

2. Run installer:

	sudo /mnt/cdrom/install

3. Select Use File Installation Key.

4. Select I have Installation Key for my license and provide:

	09806-07443-53955-64350-21751-41297

To install Matlab Production Server,using this
	40236-45817-26714-51426-39281

5. Install into folder: /usr/local/MATLAB/R2017b

6. Wait for request of DVD2:

	sudo umount /mnt/cdrom
	sudo mount [Downloader.ga]R2018a_glnxa64_dvd2.iso /mnt/cdrom/ -o loop

7. Continue with installation and wait for finish.

8. Replace libmwlmgrimpl.so:

	sudo cp -R [Downloader.ga]MATLAB\ R2018a\ Linux64\ Crack/R2018a/bin /usr/local/MATLAB/R2018a/

8. Run MATLAB for the first time:

	sudo /usr/local/MATLAB/R2018a/bin/matlab

9. Select Activate manually without Internet and provide:

	[Downloader.ga]MATLAB R2018a Linux64 Crack/license_standalone.lic

The license will appear in /usr/local/MATLAB/R2017b/licenses.

10. Run activated MATLAB:

	sudo /usr/local/MATLAB/R2018a/bin/matlab

Enjoy MATLAB! Or think about numpy/scipy or Octave :)

The previous guide was tested on Fedora 24 and works well!
